  "translations": {
    "en": "When the people entered the house for the consultation, al-Miqdad ibn al-Aswad al-Kindi - may Allah bless him with mercy - came and said: \"Allow me in with you, for I have sincere counsel for the sake of Allah and something good for you.\" They refused. Then he said: \"Allow my head in and listen to me.\" They refused him even that. Then he said: \"Since you refuse, then do not swear allegiance to a man who did not witness Badr, nor pledge the allegiance of al-Ridwan, and who fled on the day of Uhud when the two groups met.\"",
